 34CL    33S(P,G)                      1983WA27,1977DA02,1992KA39ENSDF    202609
 34CL  H TYP=FUL$AUT=LIJIE SUN AND JUN CHEN$CIT=ENSDF$CUT=30-Sep-2026$          
 34CL  H TYP=FUL$AUT=NINEL NICA, BALRAJ SINGH$CIT=NDS 113, 1563 (2012)$         
 34CL2 H CUT=28-May-2012$                                                       
 34CL c  {+33}S+1p|){+34}Cl from J|p=3/2+ {+33}S ground state.                  
 34CL c  1983Wa27: 0.4-2.0-MeV proton beams were provided from the 2.5-MV Van de
 34CL2c  Graaff accelerator at Potchefstroom University, South Africa. The      
 34CL3c  targets were Ag{-2}S (92%-enriched in {+33}S) on Ta backings. |g rays  
 34CL4c  were detected using a NaI detector and two Ge(Li) detectors. Measured  
 34CL5c  E|g, I|g, |g(|q). Deduced reaction Q values, J, |p, 41 bound levels, 41
 34CL6c  resonance strengths, and lifetimes for 17 bound levels using DSAM.     
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1977Da02: 1.0-2.0-MeV proton beams were provided from the 4-MV Van de  
 34CL2c  Graaff accelerator at CENBG, France. The targets were Ag{-2}S          
 34CL3c  (92%-enriched in {+33}S) on Au backings. |g rays were detected using a 
 34CL4c  NaI detector and two Ge(Li) detectors. Measured E|g, I|g, and radiative
 34CL5c  capture excitation functions. Deduced reaction Q values, levels, 45    
 34CL6c  resonance strengths, |g-ray branching ratios, and lifetimes using DSAM.
 34CL c  1977Da03: similar setup as 1977Da02. Protons were detected using four  
 34CL2c  Si(Li) surface barrier detectors. Measured excitation functions for    
 34CL3c  (p,p) elastic scattering. Deduced |g multipole mixing ratios, resonance
 34CL4c  energies, J, and |p from an R-matrix fit on (p,p) excitation functions.
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1992Ka39: 1.8-3.5-MeV proton beams impinged on a Ag{-2}S target. |g    
 34CL2c  rays were detected using Ge(Li) and NaI(Tl) detectors. Measured E|g,   
 34CL3c  I|g, and |g(|q). Deduced J, |p, and |g multipolarities and multipole   
 34CL4c  mixing ratios.                                                         
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  2020Pa40: a 1.072-MeV proton beam was produced from the 5U 5-MV        
 34CL2c  single-ended vertical Pelletron at the Nuclear Science Laboratory of   
 34CL3c  University of Notre Dame. The target was prepared by implanting 70-keV 
 34CL4c  negative {+33}S ions into a tantalum foil. |g rays were detected with  
 34CL5c  the compact detector array GEORGINA, consisting of five Ge detectors.  
 34CL6c  Measured E|g, I|g, |g|g-coin. Deduced precise |g-ray branching ratios  
 34CL7c  for the 666-keV level.                                                 
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  2013Fa10: Direct measurement of the {+33}S(p,|g){+34}Cl reaction in    
 34CL2c  inverse kinematics using 194-514 keV/nucleon {+33}S beams produced from
 34CL3c  the Isotope Separator and Accelerator (ISAC) radioactive beam facility 
 34CL4c  at TRIUMF. The beams impinged on a windowless gas target of H{-2} gas  
 34CL5c  on the DRAGON (Detector of Recoils And Gammas Of Nuclear reactions)    
 34CL6c  recoil separator. |g rays from radiative captures were detected by 30  
 34CL7c  BGO detectors surrounding the target. Recoil products were separated by
 34CL8c  the DRAGON separator and detected in a double-sided silicon strip      
 34CL9c  detector (DSSSD) at the end. Measured E|g, reaction yields. Discovered 
 34CLAc  two new resonances. Deduced resonance energies (E{-r}) and resonance   
 34CLBc  strengths (|w|g). Summarized in Conference proceedings 2010PaZT.       
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  2011Fr04: Direct measurement of the {+33}S(p,|g){+34}Cl reaction in    
 34CL2c  normal kinematics using 200-710 keV proton beams provided from a tandem
 34CL3c  Van de Graaff accelerator at the University of Washington. Targets were
 34CL4c  prepared by implanting 45-keV 10{+16} {+33}S ions into oxygen-free     
 34CL5c  high-conductivity copper substrates. |g rays were detected using two   
 34CL6c  HPGe detectors at |+55|', surrounded by plastic scintillators operating
 34CL7c  in anticoincidence mode. Measured E|g and I|g for three resonances at  
 34CL8c  432, 492, and 529 keV. Deduced precise |g-ray branching ratios for the 
 34CL9c  three resonances and the percentage of decays producing {+34}Cl g.s.   
 34CLAc  and {+34m}Cl at 147 keV. Summarized in Conference proceedings 2010PaZT.
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1994Li20: 0.973-1.997-MeV proton beams were provided from the AURA2    
 34CL2c  accelerator at the University of Auckland, New Zealand and impinged on 
 34CL3c  Ag{-2}S targets 98%-enriched in {+33}S. |g rays were detected by a 22% 
 34CL4c  Ge(Li) at 90|' relative to the beam direction and a NaI detector.      
 34CL5c  Positrons from {+34}Cl decay were detected by a plastic scintillator   
 34CL6c  |DE-E telescope. A separate measurement was performed using the proton 
 34CL7c  beams from the 3 MeV Van de Graaff laboratory at the University of     
 34CL8c  Florence, Italy. |g rays were detected using an 80% intrinsic Ge       
 34CL9c  detector. Measured E|g, I|g, and positron yields. Deduced              
 34CLAc  {+33}S(p,|g){+34}Cl reaction Q values, S(p) of {+34}Cl, and precise    
 34CLBc  excitation energies for three resonances.                              
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1985La16: 1.05-1.98-MeV proton beams were provided from the 2.5-MV Van 
 34CL2c  de Graaff accelerator at the University of Helsinki and impinged on    
 34CL3c  {+33}S targets on Ta backings. |g rays were detected using a PGT       
 34CL4c  110-cm{+3} Ge(Li) detector. Deduced lifetimes for 35 bound levels using
 34CL5c  DSAM.                                                                  
 34CL c  1984Ke01: 0.82- and 1.43-MeV proton beams were provided from the 2.5-MV
 34CL2c  Van de Graaff accelerator at the University of Helsinki and impinged on
 34CL3c  {+33}S targets on Ta backings. |g rays were detected using a PGT Ge(Li)
 34CL4c  detector. Deduced lifetimes for two bound levels using DSAM.           
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1983Ra04: 0.9-1.4-MeV proton beams impinged on an 88.2%-enriched {+33}S
 34CL2c  target (CdS on carbon backing). |g rays were detected using a NaI      
 34CL3c  detector at 90|' relative to the beam direction and protons were       
 34CL4c  detected using a Si surface barrier detector at 135|' relative to the  
 34CL5c  beam direction. Measured E|g, I|g, reaction Q, and S(p).               
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1973An13: 1.3-1.8-MeV proton beams were provided from the 2.5-MV van de
 34CL2c  Graaff accelerator at the University of Helsinki and impinged on {+33}S
 34CL3c  targets on Ta backings. |g rays were detected using a 40-cm{+3} Ge(Li) 
 34CL4c  detector. Measured E|g, I|g. Deduced levels and lifetimes using DSAM.  
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1971Hy02: 1058, 1098, 1121-keV proton beams were provided from the     
 34CL2c  Aerospace Research Laboratories 2-MeV Van de Graaff accelerator and    
 34CL3c  impinged on an 84%-enriched {+33}S target (Ag backing soldered on brass
 34CL4c  disk). |g rays were detected using a Ge(Li) detector and a NaI         
 34CL5c  detector. Measured E|g, I|g, and p|g(|q). Deduced levels, J, |p,       
 34CL6c  resonance strengths for three resonances, |g multipolarities, and      
 34CL7c  multipole mixing ratios.                                               
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1969Gr29: 1.0-1.3-MeV proton beams impinged on a 25%-enriched {+33}S   
 34CL2c  target. |g rays were detected using a Ge(Li) detector at 0|' and 115|' 
 34CL3c  or 120|' relative to the beam direction. Measured E|g, I|g, p|g(|q),   
 34CL4c  and p|g(|q). Deduced levels, J, |p, |g multipolarities, multipole      
 34CL5c  mixing ratios, and lifetimes using DSAM.                               
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  1964Gl04: 0.3-1.3-MeV proton beams impinged on a 22%-enriched {+33}S   
 34CL2c  target (CdS on Cu or Ta backings). |g rays were detected using NaI     
 34CL3c  detectors at +85|' and -85|' relative to the beam direction. Measured  
 34CL4c  E|g, I|g, |g|g-coin for nine resonances (E{-p}(lab)=447, 507, 546, 639,
 34CL5c  662, 683, 731, 777, 822 keV). Deduced resonance strengths.             
 34CL c  1959Ku79: protons were accelerated with the Utrecht 850-kV             
 34CL2c  Cockcroft-Walton generator and impinged on a CdS target enriched in    
 34CL3c  {+33}S. Measured |g-ray yield curves. Deduced two resonances.          
 34CL d                                                                         
 34CL c  Standard definition of resonance strength                              
 34CL2c  |w|g=(2J{-r}+1)/[(2J{-p}+1)(2J{-T}+1)]|*|G{-|g}|G{-p}/|G, where J{-r}  
 34CL3c  is the spin of the resonance, J{-p}=1/2 is the spin of the proton, and 
 34CL4c  J{-T}=3/2 is the spin of the target {+33}S ground state. The resonance 
 34CL5c  strengths S from the original papers in this dataset are mainly        
 34CL6c  obtained from resonance |g-ray yields and are defined without the      
 34CL7c  (2J{-p}+1)(2J{-T}+1) factor. Therefore, to obtain the standard         
 34CL8c  resonance strength, all the resonance strengths provided in the        
 34CL9c  comments below should be divided by 8, except for |w|g values from     
 34CLAc  2013Fa10, which are already in the standard definition.                
 34CL cG E$From level-energy differences, unless otherwise noted.               
 34CL cG RI$From 1983Wa27, unless otherwise noted.                              
 34CL cG RI(D)$From 1977Da02.                                                   
 34CL cG RI(F)$From 2011Fr04                                                    
 34CL cG M,MR$From |g(|q) and/or |g|g(|q) data given under comments.            
 34CL cL E$For resonances above S(p)({+34}Cl)=5143.20 {I5} (2021Wa16),          
 34CL2cL E(level)=E{-c.m.}+S(p)({+34}Cl), where                                 
 34CL3cL E{-c.m.}=E{-p}(lab)|*m({+33}S)/[m{-p}+m({+33}S)], unless otherwise     
 34CL4cL noted. For levels below 7.08 MeV (E{-p}(lab)<2 MeV), E{-p}(lab) is     
 34CL5cL mainly from 1964Gl04, 1977Da02, and 1983Wa27. The average is taken when
 34CL6cL multiple E{-p}(lab) values are available. For levels above 7.08 MeV    
 34CL7cL (E{-p}(lab)>2 MeV), E{-p}(lab) is mainly from 1992Ka39.                
 34CL cL E$Most papers in this dataset report precise E(level) values based on  
 34CL2cL E|g data without reporting their measured E|g values. The only         
 34CL3cL exception is 1964Gl04, which reports E|g measured by a NaI detector    
 34CL4cL with uncertainties ranging from 10 to 50 keV. In addition to the large 
 34CL5cL uncertainties, 1964Gl04 also used a much lower S(p)({+34}Cl)=5.12 MeV  
 34CL6cL in their analysis, which contributes to generally lower E(level)       
 34CL7cL values. A least-squares fit to available E|g values with uncertainties 
 34CL8cL would not yield E(level) values that are more precise or complete than 
 34CL9cL those already reported in the original papers. Therefore, the          
 34CLAcL evaluators have adopted the precise E(level) values reported in papers 
 34CLBcL and the average is taken when multiple E(level) values are available.  
 34CL cL J$For low-lying levels with J and |p that are both given, J|p is from  
 34CL2cL the Adopted Levels. For other levels, J is from the comparison of      
 34CL3cL experimental angular distributions of |g-rays with theoretical         
 34CL4cL predictions or deduced from |g-feedings, unless otherwise noted.       
 34CL cL S$From 1992Ka39, unless otherwise noted.                               
 34CL cL S$LABEL=E{-p}(lab) (keV)                                               
